cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the convergence and optimality of a popular machine learning algorithm, Generative Adversarial Imitation Learning (GAIL), with neural networks. It also involves the analysis of a gradient-based algorithm, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics) as GAIL is often used in these fields. The use of neural networks also suggests that the paper may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Finally, the paper's focus on convergence and optimality may also make it relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
